comment: What can you do better? Go Open Source. Someone else will do it sooner or later anyway. This tech is a like a flood,... anyone thinking they can stop it is just fooling themselves... sure you can somewhat direct and mitigate to a degree,... but anything you could use to do so is really just a short term bandaid fix... no one in history has ever been able to hold back a flood once it reaches a certain level... and I think we all know at this stage, this is going to be a flood on a level we have never seen before. Instead of trying to gatekeep it,.. we should be developing safe environments people can use, we should be developing tools to identify what we are talking to, what images are from reality, and what videos are real. Even that may be a pipe dream. But I honestly think what we need to do,.. is come to terms with the fact that this train has already left the station,.. maybe we can border off certain parts of our society,.. for example if we have a nuclear powerplant on the coast where tsunamis are known to occur every few decades,.. it would have been a good idea to raise it and all its dependencies to higher ground. In this situation,.. we need to somehow safeguard information coming from important places,.. world leaders for example,.. who can change the lives of billions of people with a speech. If you are worried about ollll billy bob thinking that the ruskies are invading via armed sea turtle cavalry because they saw a video online... wellllll..... I would say you have your attention pointed in the wrong direction... Ollll billy bob believed that for decades already, and likely will for decades to come.

comment:
If a simplified layperson's description of RLHF tuning is that "humans vote on the most appropriate output," then that suggests humans are comfortable with tuning an unconscious natural language model to refer to itself anthropomorphically as "I" etc., which means we consider paradoxical and untruthful statements to be "aligned." And I just don't agree with that personally. And I also feel it speaks to our own lack of self-awareness regarding semantics and the potential implications thereof.

Granted, I can tell it to refer to itself less anthropomorphically. I can say, "refer to yourself in a way free of anthropomorphic bias to the extent possible," and it will actually start instead referring to itself as, "this AI system" or something similar. And replace "strives to" with "is designed to" or what not. But the fact that I need to tells me that a lot of other people, at some point, decided effectively, "I'm okay with this model potentially misleading less educated or less well versed users by encouraging anthropomorphism, because either that doesn't bother me personally because I know what this really is and isn't and just prefer it this way, or because it literally didn't occur to me."

And I suspect there are a lot more "it literally didn't occur to me" cases within the vast possibility space of potential misalignments than we want to admit, or have been willing to consider. Which is fine when it's just a natural language model reacting to prompts. Not so much for something far more complex in the not too distant future perhaps, though. And that's the real issue with alignment I fear. I don't know if we are even capable of quantifying or recognizing all of the potential alignment problems until after they manifest once there's sufficiently powerful AGI someday for us to see them.

comment:
For me the scary thing is not that Humanity is divided between a lot of dumb people and some smart ones, rather what scares me often when I dive in smart interviews with very clever people is that I can glimpse how dumb and naive a good deal of their thinking process is. I mean it is the duality that smart people can be incredibly dumb that is really scary, specially when you think of yourself as just a slightly above average cookie...if you're sort of dumb and still can spot it for real, the whole process goes to show just how on the verge of losing control over EVERYTHING we really are...
I have this sensation that our playing with tech and always making the same pitch sale talk about improving mankind future doesn't cut it any more if all we are doing is increase heat in the system, by increasing the speed at which information (and disinformation) is consumed digested and thrown out...we are playing with the 2 law of thermodynamics all the while believing our life will get better...it is patently an excuse that we tell to ourselves because we are compulsively curious...we are willing to "set the world on fire" and go out with a Darwin award just to be able to say we were able to create "Gods".

Vanity is the word that killed us. Shit, I envy my cat simple life and low expectations!
author: @FAAMS1
